<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-04-12T15:42:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-04-12T15:42:00-05:00" n="326" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d326">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/3810</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SJH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Shea</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-12T16:00:00-04:42">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 12, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 10 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your circular telegram 6th. In answering Embassy’s [note], Foreign
                                Office states Chile will continue to maintain her neutrality in this
                                new conflict.</p>
                            <p>Leading editorials last few days change tone, commend South American
                                solidarity, reaffirming unanimity of ABC nations, and commending the
                                action of Brazil in breaking relations with Germany.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SJH1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Shea</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>